Hey Lew,<br><br>
A &quot;former&quot; writer? Our words will live forever! Someday Ed Ramon's great grand kids will be able to brag that their great grand dad had the privilege of talking to the illustrious and handsome and dashing writer, Tom Dier. Former writer? Our words will live until somebody pulls the plug on this site or...who the hell cares?<br><br>
Many of us have been here for a year, or 6 months, or whatever, and we all feel the same need - to belong. We are just frail human beings, not supermen. And we are looking for answers. And friendship. None of us pretend to be anything more than that. Pretending don't get it here.<br><br>
I think you want to &quot;come out&quot; and that is good, But, we can go anywhere on the internet and find assholes who want to screw with Vietnam vets. In that respect you are very ordinary. <br><br>
Say what you want to say.  We welcome diverse opinions (at least I do). But, in the words of my buddy Art Varanelli, &quot;Judge No One&quot;.
